  <p>
    <strong>Quality Points</strong>. Quality points are a unit of measure that accumulates how you are doing in the group. Players must pay dues in quality points to play the games. Those dues make up the game pots. Quality points features are totally optional. The unit of measure can be in toothpicks, dimes, pennies, etc. We are trying to avoid using the word "Money"!
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>Round dues are the basic dogfight game dues. This may be the only game played. Those individual or teams with the best scores will divide the pot by some percentage and others will loose their dues.
    </li>
    <li>Skins dues. Skins is an optional game played by many groups that rewards the best score on a hole (with no ties). Most groups and the software limit this to birdies and above.
    </li>
    <li>Other dues. There are a number of other games that may be played. Groups have a option entering the quality points given to each member, if they desire. This could be closest to the hole, low round, etc
    </li>
  </ul>
  
  <p><strong>Points Pulled or +-</strong> - 
    The difference between your quota and your point total for the round. If you have a quota of 24 points and you pull 27, you are +3 for
    the round or you pulled 27 points.
  </p>
  <p><strong>* Starred, Limited, Frozen, Restricted</strong>  
    Different terms that describe the Micky Mantle rule - you have an asterisk by your score/name! This term was adopted to indicate that some 
    restrictions are applied 
    to the member or score. The most common use is that new members to a group are often restricted to a +- Maximum/Minimum points pulled 
    until there quota is established for the group.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Gross Points</strong> - 
    Basically the number of points you pulled without any restrictions. Gross points are always used to compute a new quota.
  </p>
  <p><strong>Net Points</strong> - 
    Your gross points +- any restrictions. If your quota is 21 points and you have a +-4 point restriction and pull 31 point, you gross points 
    would be 31 (+10) and net points would be 25 (+4).  Net points are only used for computing "redistribution of wealth" or pot totals.
  </p>
  
  
  
  <p>
    <strong>Tees and courses</strong>. Each course can have up to 4 tees and quotas are based on tees and one special tee that is described by local rules. Since many courses have adopted "Politically Correct" colors, The tees have names which the group can then enter a color:
  </p>
  <ul>
    <li>P(ro, Tips, Champion , Classic Blue tees.
    </li>
    <li>B(ack, Members , Classic White Tees.
    </li>
    <li>M(iddle, Senior tees, Classic Gold Tees
    </li>
    <li>F(orward, Ladies, Super Senior, Classic Red tees.
    </li>
